parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Failure due to Coolant and Transmission Fluid Mixing
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The mixing of coolant and transmission fluid can cause transmission failure, leading to loss of power, accidents, or stranding.
Premature clutch failure can cause sudden loss of power, accidents, or stranding, especially in high-stress driving conditions.
symptoms: clutch pedal sticking to the floor

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air bag sensor can cause the air bag warning light to illuminate, and in some cases, lead to unintended air bag deployment, which can cause injuries or accidents.
symptoms: The air bag warning light illuminates
the air bag sensor light blinks
the side air bag satellite sensor corrodes

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a range of issues, including dashboard warning lights, odometer failure, and failure of safety systems such as brakes and tire sensors, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: horn requires extreme force to sound.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can cause the airbag warning light to illuminate, which can lead to accidents or injuries if the airbag fails to deploy in a crash.
symptoms: horn requires extreme force to sound.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the brake lights to fail, which can lead to accidents or injuries if the vehicle is unable to stop properly.
